WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.036 --> 00:00:13.908
[ominous music]

2
00:00:13.995 --> 00:00:20.959
♪ ♪

3
00:01:04.045 --> 00:01:06.918
- [hyperventilating]

4
00:01:07.005 --> 00:01:09.834
[phone dinging]

5
00:01:09.964 --> 00:01:13.402
♪ ♪

6
00:01:13.446 --> 00:01:16.884
[tense music]

7
00:01:16.971 --> 00:01:23.978
♪ ♪

8
00:01:27.416 --> 00:01:30.376
[hyperventilating]

9
00:01:30.463 --> 00:01:33.422
[dinging continues]

10
00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:37.949
♪ ♪

11
00:01:37.992 --> 00:01:39.907
[phone clacks]

12
00:01:39.994 --> 00:01:42.823
[dinging continues]

13
00:01:42.910 --> 00:01:48.220
♪ ♪

14
00:01:48.350 --> 00:01:51.266
[knife clatters]

15
00:01:51.353 --> 00:01:55.270
♪ ♪

16
00:01:55.401 --> 00:01:58.360
[phone ringing]

17
00:01:58.447 --> 00:02:05.411
♪ ♪

18
00:02:18.250 --> 00:02:21.079
[phone continues ringing]

19
00:02:21.209 --> 00:02:28.173
♪ ♪

20
00:02:40.751 --> 00:02:44.145
[Nicholas Franchise.
"Half Polite"]

21
00:02:44.232 --> 00:02:46.495
♪ You think you're
so half polite ♪

22
00:02:46.583 --> 00:02:49.107
♪ But I'm not
with you in mind ♪

23
00:02:49.150 --> 00:02:51.544
♪ I am not with you tonight

24
00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:53.764
♪ I've tried and tried

25
00:02:53.807 --> 00:02:56.157
♪ You think you're
so half polite ♪

26
00:02:56.288 --> 00:02:58.769
♪ But I'm not
with you in mind ♪

27
00:02:58.812 --> 00:03:00.901
♪ I am not with you tonight

28
00:03:00.988 --> 00:03:02.947
♪ I've tried and tried ♪

29
00:03:03.034 --> 00:03:05.732
♪ But you think you're
so half polite ♪

30
00:03:05.776 --> 00:03:08.256
♪ But I'm not
with you in mind ♪

31
00:03:08.343 --> 00:03:10.737
♪ I am not with you tonight ♪

32
00:03:10.781 --> 00:03:12.521
♪ I've tried and tried

33
00:03:12.652 --> 00:03:15.089
♪ You think you're
so half polite ♪

34
00:03:15.133 --> 00:03:17.570
♪ But I'm not
with you in mind ♪

35
00:03:17.657 --> 00:03:19.093
♪ I am not with you ♪

36
00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:20.094
- Georgie!

37
00:03:20.181 --> 00:03:21.052
- Catherine.

38
00:03:21.182 --> 00:03:23.097
♪ I've tried and tried ♪

39
00:03:24.788 --> 00:03:27.373
We're taking a trip to the countryside
for our one year anniversary.

40
00:03:32.237 --> 00:03:34.674
- ♪ You think you're
so half polite ♪

41
00:03:34.761 --> 00:03:37.111
♪ But I'm not with
you in my mine ♪

42
00:03:37.198 --> 00:03:39.374
♪ I am not with you tonight ♪

43
00:03:39.505 --> 00:03:41.681
♪ I've tried and tried ♪

44
00:03:41.768 --> 00:03:44.205
♪ You think you're
so half polite ♪

45
00:03:44.336 --> 00:03:46.773
♪ But I'm not
with you in mind ♪

46
00:03:46.817 --> 00:03:49.167
♪ I'm not with you tonight

47
00:03:55.913 --> 00:03:56.827
- She's back.

48
00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:57.828
- Heya.

49
00:03:57.737 --> 00:03:58.655
Hey Catherine!

50
00:03:59.155 --> 00:04:00.490
I'll talk to you later. mom.

51
00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:02.325
I want to see you both again soon. come visit.

52
00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:03.493
Catherine tell her.

53
00:04:03.493 --> 00:04:06.246
I keep telling her we should
come up.

54
00:04:06.663 --> 00:04:08.998
Talk soon. mom.

55
00:04:08.998 --> 00:04:11.084
See you both soon.

56
00:04:13.104 --> 00:04:15.802
- Georgie was asking for you.

57
00:04:15.889 --> 00:04:19.327
I told him you hated him and
that you despised his baking.

58
00:04:22.113 --> 00:04:23.201
- You bitch.

59
00:04:23.244 --> 00:04:25.769
[soft piano music]

60
00:04:25.849 --> 00:04:31.938
So. thinking. I've been saving up some off time.
maybe we could finally go and see America.

61
00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:34.858
I don't think so.

62
00:04:34.858 --> 00:04:36.192
See your family.

63
00:04:36.192 --> 00:04:38.611
I've been dying to see New York.

64
00:04:38.956 --> 00:04:39.957
- You wouldn't like my family.

65
00:04:41.614 --> 00:04:43.366
You haven't seen them in years.

66
00:04:47.921 --> 00:04:49.923
- I'm excited for this weekend.

67
00:04:50.010 --> 00:04:51.316
- We could have just
done something here.

68
00:04:51.446 --> 00:04:52.839
- Well. I wanted to.

69
00:04:52.883 --> 00:04:55.233
I want this weekend
to be special.

70
00:04:55.363 --> 00:04:56.364
It's a big deal.

71
00:04:58.976 --> 00:04:59.890
- I guess.

72
00:05:02.936 --> 00:05:04.416
It's just too much.

73
00:05:04.503 --> 00:05:05.678
- Well. I keep saying I
can help pay for things.

74
00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:10.643
You're a broke transient international student. I'm sure.

75
00:05:13.991 --> 00:05:16.733
[birds chirping]

76
00:05:18.735 --> 00:05:20.127
- Where'd you get that?

77
00:05:20.214 --> 00:05:21.346
- I rented it.

78
00:05:23.391 --> 00:05:26.090
It's a weekend. not a month.

79
00:05:26.177 --> 00:05:29.136
[Mont Duamel. "New Light"]

80
00:05:29.223 --> 00:05:36.100
♪ ♪

81
00:05:56.598 --> 00:05:58.992
- Oh. wow.

82
00:05:59.123 --> 00:06:01.038
Let's pull over.

83
00:06:01.125 --> 00:06:02.343
- We're already an hour behind

84
00:06:02.387 --> 00:06:03.344
- Oh. come on.

85
00:06:03.388 --> 00:06:04.432
It'll be quick.

86
00:06:04.476 --> 00:06:05.869
I love this kind of stuff.

87
00:06:05.956 --> 00:06:12.919
♪ ♪

88
00:06:38.553 --> 00:06:39.511
Let's go upstairs.

89
00:06:43.820 --> 00:06:44.821
Come on!

90
00:07:00.140 --> 00:07:00.924
- Step back from there.

91
00:07:01.054 --> 00:07:02.186
It's dangerous.

92
00:07:02.273 --> 00:07:03.752
- It's fine.

93
00:07:03.840 --> 00:07:05.363
- Diane.

94
00:07:05.450 --> 00:07:06.451
- It's fine.

95
00:07:11.456 --> 00:07:12.544
Stand there.

96
00:07:35.393 --> 00:07:37.656
[camera clicks]

97
00:07:37.786 --> 00:07:40.789
[Mont Duamel. "New Light"]

98
00:07:40.877 --> 00:07:47.753
♪ ♪

99
00:07:54.760 --> 00:07:56.980
- We booked the corner
top room suite. though.

100
00:07:57.067 --> 00:07:58.198
I'm confused.

101
00:07:58.285 --> 00:07:59.852
- My apologies.

102
00:07:59.983 --> 00:08:01.419
We've had a bit of a reshuffle
with a special guest who

103
00:08:01.549 --> 00:08:02.637
just showed up last minute.

104
00:08:02.681 --> 00:08:04.117
- A special guest?
- Yes.

105
00:08:04.204 --> 00:08:05.162
How do I say it?

106
00:08:05.205 --> 00:08:06.859
A marketing deal.

107
00:08:06.946 --> 00:08:08.513
Our dates got moved
around. and my apologies.

108
00:08:08.600 --> 00:08:10.863
- I spent extra on that
room specifically.

109
00:08:10.950 --> 00:08:12.734
We've been planning
this trip for months.

110
00:08:12.865 --> 00:08:14.171
- Again. we are very sorry.

111
00:08:17.696 --> 00:08:19.306
- All good?

112
00:08:19.393 --> 00:08:20.438
- Not really.

113
00:08:22.788 --> 00:08:25.312
It's tiny.

114
00:08:25.443 --> 00:08:26.444
- It's fine.

115
00:08:29.795 --> 00:08:32.798
[rooster crowing]

116
00:08:35.279 --> 00:08:37.803
I am just excited to spend
some time off with you.

117
00:08:41.546 --> 00:08:44.462
[birds chirping]

118
00:08:46.246 --> 00:08:49.119
[background chatter]

119
00:08:53.732 --> 00:08:56.430
- Slightly boring
at this point.

120
00:08:56.561 --> 00:08:58.215
Do you get what-- no.

121
00:08:58.258 --> 00:09:01.044
No. I told him that we needed
the flight on Thursday.

122
00:09:01.087 --> 00:09:02.480
not Friday.

123
00:09:02.610 --> 00:09:04.569
He is utterly incompetent.
and this place

124
00:09:04.699 --> 00:09:06.397
is nothing like they said.

125
00:09:06.527 --> 00:09:07.876
I don't know what they're
expecting me to do with it.

126
00:09:07.964 --> 00:09:10.357
It's in the middle of nowhere.

127
00:09:10.488 --> 00:09:12.055
No. I know.

128
00:09:12.185 --> 00:09:15.928
But. oh. the room is not
what they sold me on.

129
00:09:16.015 --> 00:09:18.887
It is so small.

130
00:09:18.931 --> 00:09:19.932
I'll be fine.

131
00:09:20.019 --> 00:09:20.977
I'll figure it out.

132
00:09:21.107 --> 00:09:22.195
It's just a couple of days.

133
00:09:22.326 --> 00:09:23.153
[sighs]

134
00:09:23.283 --> 00:09:24.632
Yeah.

135
00:09:24.676 --> 00:09:25.677
I'll speak to you soon.

136
00:09:28.506 --> 00:09:29.942
[sighs]

137
00:09:37.994 --> 00:09:39.430
The pool is kind
of small. isn't it?

138
00:09:39.517 --> 00:09:42.041
It looked bigger
in the pictures.

139
00:09:42.085 --> 00:09:45.044
I don't know what
I'm gonna do with it.

140
00:09:45.131 --> 00:09:46.176
Charlotte. by the way.

141
00:09:46.306 --> 00:09:47.351
- Hmm?

142
00:09:50.006 --> 00:09:52.008
- I wasn't originally
gonna come.

143
00:09:52.051 --> 00:09:54.575
but then they ended up comping
the whole thing last minute.

144
00:09:54.619 --> 00:09:57.839
And I have. like.
a deal with the chain.

145
00:09:57.970 --> 00:09:59.885
so I'm sort of forced to come.

146
00:10:02.279 --> 00:10:03.889
- The pool looks
bigger in their photos.

147
00:10:03.976 --> 00:10:06.500
Why not just make it look
bigger in your photos?

148
00:10:09.634 --> 00:10:11.940
- What's your name?

149
00:10:11.984 --> 00:10:14.856
- Catherine.

150
00:10:14.943 --> 00:10:18.730
- Well. lovely to meet you.

151
00:10:23.517 --> 00:10:25.476
- [sighs]

152
00:10:34.267 --> 00:10:35.703
[chatter]

153
00:10:37.096 --> 00:10:39.838
[loud laughter]

154
00:10:44.930 --> 00:10:47.585
[chatter. laughter]

155
00:10:52.807 --> 00:10:55.636
[eerie music]

156
00:10:55.723 --> 00:11:02.730
♪ ♪

157
00:11:10.651 --> 00:11:12.871
- She feels bad.

158
00:11:12.914 --> 00:11:14.960
- I highly doubt that.

159
00:11:15.091 --> 00:11:16.353
You should have seen
how she was talking

160
00:11:16.396 --> 00:11:19.138
to her assistant or whoever.

161
00:11:19.225 --> 00:11:22.098
- She even offered
to swap rooms.

162
00:11:22.185 --> 00:11:23.360
- Try taking her up on it.

163
00:11:26.928 --> 00:11:30.367
- Look. she wants
to buy us dinner.

164
00:11:30.497 --> 00:11:32.630
If you don't want to go.
it's fine. but I'm going.

165
00:11:36.503 --> 00:11:39.289
[piano playing]

166
00:11:39.376 --> 00:11:41.073
♪ ♪

167
00:11:41.160 --> 00:11:42.857
- Honestly. I was bouncing
back and forth between LA

168
00:11:42.988 --> 00:11:45.338
and New York doing
makeup sponsorships.

169
00:11:45.382 --> 00:11:47.340
Basically. selling
products to little girls.

170
00:11:47.427 --> 00:11:49.299
And then I got
pulled back to Europe

171
00:11:49.386 --> 00:11:50.952
for these travel campaigns. and
now I'm ready for something

172
00:11:51.039 --> 00:11:52.650
new again.

173
00:11:52.737 --> 00:11:54.217
- You don't get lonely
traveling all alone?

174
00:11:54.304 --> 00:11:55.305
- No.

175
00:11:55.435 --> 00:11:57.394
I am constantly meeting people.

176
00:11:57.524 --> 00:12:00.397
And plenty of creators are
solo travelers. so you get

177
00:12:00.484 --> 00:12:01.615
to know people along the way.

178
00:12:01.746 --> 00:12:03.574
- I don't know
if I could do it.

179
00:12:03.661 --> 00:12:05.445
I feel like I'd feel unsafe
traveling by myself like that.

180
00:12:05.489 --> 00:12:07.273
- Yeah. it seems risky.

181
00:12:07.317 --> 00:12:09.188
Nobody really knows
where you are.

182
00:12:09.319 --> 00:12:12.060
- Well. what's life
without a little risk?

183
00:12:12.148 --> 00:12:13.714
- You've traveled solo before.

184
00:12:13.801 --> 00:12:14.802
- Not really.

185
00:12:14.889 --> 00:12:16.717
Only Europe.

186
00:12:16.804 --> 00:12:19.503
- When the two of us met. she
seemed so down on herself.

187
00:12:19.633 --> 00:12:21.244
didn't seem to know anyone.

188
00:12:21.374 --> 00:12:26.640
And then she just came
and swept me off of my feet.

189
00:12:26.684 --> 00:12:28.076
- You two are together?

190
00:12:28.164 --> 00:12:29.948
Oh my god!

191
00:12:29.991 --> 00:12:35.432
[laughs] I thought you
were sisters or something.

192
00:12:35.562 --> 00:12:36.476
- Sisters.

193
00:12:36.607 --> 00:12:39.392
- Oh. this is so cute.

194
00:12:39.479 --> 00:12:41.220
- I mean. this is
actually our anniversary.

195
00:12:41.307 --> 00:12:42.526
- [gasps]
- A whole year.

196
00:12:42.613 --> 00:12:44.223
- Oh my god.

197
00:12:44.310 --> 00:12:45.268
And I'm here. just. like.
ruining the whole thing.

198
00:12:45.355 --> 00:12:46.312
[laughs]

199
00:12:46.443 --> 00:12:48.532
- No. that's okay.

200
00:12:48.662 --> 00:12:50.838
- So what have you got planned?

201
00:12:50.969 --> 00:12:53.754
- Yeah. we're thinking of going
out to the countrysides.

202
00:12:53.841 --> 00:12:55.582
maybe see a vineyard.

203
00:12:55.713 --> 00:12:59.456
- Oh. I actually have
this exclusive wine

204
00:12:59.543 --> 00:13:01.371
tour happening tomorrow.

205
00:13:01.458 --> 00:13:02.546
Sponsor thing.

206
00:13:02.589 --> 00:13:04.243
I could get you guys an invite.

207
00:13:04.330 --> 00:13:05.331
- We have our own plans.

208
00:13:08.987 --> 00:13:10.945
- [clears throat]

209
00:13:11.032 --> 00:13:13.861
So how long have
you been in France?

210
00:13:16.516 --> 00:13:17.691
- Me?

211
00:13:17.735 --> 00:13:18.736
- Yeah.

212
00:13:18.823 --> 00:13:20.564
You're American. no?

213
00:13:20.651 --> 00:13:23.610
- Yeah. but I've been in Europe
for a number of years.

214
00:13:23.697 --> 00:13:25.525
- America is so new.

215
00:13:25.656 --> 00:13:28.311
There's something about modern
cities that just speaks to me.

216
00:13:28.398 --> 00:13:29.616
- Greener grass. I guess.

217
00:13:29.703 --> 00:13:30.704
- Totally.

218
00:13:30.791 --> 00:13:32.010
So much more lush.

219
00:13:32.097 --> 00:13:33.968
I just got back from
Japan. and I got

220
00:13:34.012 --> 00:13:35.666
the most beautiful pictures.

221
00:13:35.796 --> 00:13:38.059
- Oh. Catherine's always
wanted to go see Asia.

222
00:13:38.146 --> 00:13:40.279
We think we might
try to go next year.

223
00:13:40.366 --> 00:13:41.324
- You've never been?

224
00:13:41.411 --> 00:13:42.368
- No.

225
00:13:42.412 --> 00:13:43.804
Bucket list. I guess.

226
00:13:43.891 --> 00:13:46.111
- I mean. you're always
talking about it.

227
00:13:46.242 --> 00:13:49.201
- Well. everyone's
gotta start somewhere.

228
00:13:49.288 --> 00:13:52.030
I'm actually thinking about
going back to Bali once Europe

229
00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:53.553
inevitably bores me.

230
00:13:53.597 --> 00:13:55.642
I've got some
friends in Thailand.

231
00:13:55.686 --> 00:13:59.951
and I'm definitely
so jealous. [laughs]

232
00:14:02.867 --> 00:14:04.738
[chuckling]

233
00:14:04.825 --> 00:14:06.653
- She's nice.

234
00:14:06.784 --> 00:14:08.829
- Sure.

235
00:14:08.873 --> 00:14:09.830
- She means well.

236
00:14:09.874 --> 00:14:12.093
I don't mind her.

237
00:14:12.180 --> 00:14:14.444
She apparently helps
run this charity.

238
00:14:14.531 --> 00:14:16.489
- It's just the entitlement.

239
00:14:16.576 --> 00:14:18.709
Girls like that
just take and take.

240
00:14:18.796 --> 00:14:20.363
But if you take
their phones away.

241
00:14:20.406 --> 00:14:23.409
they'd be completely
useless. dead in a week.

242
00:14:23.540 --> 00:14:25.193
- Are you jealous?

243
00:14:25.281 --> 00:14:26.325
- What?

244
00:14:26.412 --> 00:14:28.240
No.

245
00:14:28.284 --> 00:14:29.894
I just think girls like that
are single-handedly ruining

246
00:14:29.981 --> 00:14:31.722
the next generation of women.

247
00:14:31.809 --> 00:14:34.333
Someone should
teach them a lesson.

248
00:14:34.377 --> 00:14:35.987
A little isolation
without their phones

249
00:14:36.074 --> 00:14:37.423
would probably do them good.

250
00:14:37.467 --> 00:14:39.033
- Always so dramatic.

251
00:14:39.120 --> 00:14:41.384
- When I was a kid. I
spent a lot of time alone.

252
00:14:41.427 --> 00:14:42.385
Did me good.

253
00:14:42.472 --> 00:14:43.864
- What?

254
00:14:43.995 --> 00:14:46.302
Like. strand them all
alone with no phone

255
00:14:46.389 --> 00:14:48.565
service and see how
long they survive?

256
00:14:48.652 --> 00:14:52.177
- See. now you're talking
like a psychopath.

257
00:14:52.220 --> 00:14:55.441
- It would make
a good reality show.

258
00:14:55.528 --> 00:14:57.922
- I bet no one would
notice if she disappeared.

259
00:14:58.052 --> 00:14:59.967
- What are you looking at?

260
00:15:00.054 --> 00:15:01.012
- Nothing.

261
00:15:04.929 --> 00:15:08.367
Tomorrow. let's go
to the countryside.

262
00:15:08.454 --> 00:15:10.108
Just you and me.

263
00:15:10.238 --> 00:15:11.544
What we came here for.

264
00:15:11.588 --> 00:15:13.894
- Mm.

265
00:15:13.938 --> 00:15:15.026
I'd like that.

266
00:15:24.818 --> 00:15:26.733
[rooster crowing]

267
00:15:26.820 --> 00:15:29.693
- [groans]

268
00:15:42.053 --> 00:15:44.838
- You're up early.

269
00:15:44.882 --> 00:15:47.841
Look at you. all done up.

270
00:15:47.885 --> 00:15:51.279
[chuckles] Ah. yeah. you.

271
00:15:51.367 --> 00:15:54.239
Long black with milk
and a little bowl of fruit.

272
00:15:54.326 --> 00:15:55.371
Diane's still asleep?

273
